NAME
    App::XTermUtils - Utilities related to XTerm

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of App::XTermUtils (from Perl
    distribution App-XTermUtils), released on 2018-09-25.

DESCRIPTION
    This distribution provides the following command-line utilities:

    *   get-term-bgcolor

    *   set-term-bgcolor

FUNCTIONS
  get_term_bgcolor
    Usage:

     get_term_bgcolor() -> [status, msg, result, meta]

    Get terminal background color.

    This function is not exported.

    No arguments.

    Returns an enveloped result (an array).

    First element (status) is an integer containing HTTP status code (200
    means OK, 4xx caller error, 5xx function error). Second element (msg) is
    a string containing error message, or 'OK' if status is 200. Third
    element (result) is optional, the actual result. Fourth element (meta)
    is called result metadata and is optional, a hash that contains extra
    information.

    Return value: (any)

  set_term_bgcolor
    Usage:

     set_term_bgcolor(%args) -> [status, msg, result, meta]

    Set terminal background color.

    This function is not exported.

    Arguments ('*' denotes required arguments):

    *   rgb* => *color::rgb24*

    Returns an enveloped result (an array).

    First element (status) is an integer containing HTTP status code (200
    means OK, 4xx caller error, 5xx function error). Second element (msg) is
    a string containing error message, or 'OK' if status is 200. Third
    element (result) is optional, the actual result. Fourth element (meta)
    is called result metadata and is optional, a hash that contains extra
    information.

    Return value: (any)

